I like the concept, but nothing here really feels new. There's already an alien/unnatural ecosystem SCP-217 covers the clockwork angle. I think this needs a rewrite to make it more unique from those two.

I want to know more about the ecosystem aspect. Most of this SCP sounds like it's just a robo-bug generator, but then you touch on a food-chain and stuff. That sounds like it could be very interesting, and would help round out concept, give it some depth. I don't really want a list of bugs, I want to know how the ecosystem functions as a whole, and why, if got loose, it would be a problem. How quickly do the herbivore machines eat, were these machines found in just one room, stuck in a loop of eating only themselves, or were they spreading slowly from the clock?

I'm not going to vote, because I don't dislike it, but it needs something more.







