There is a conflict in the containment/description:

Under Containment - any containment breach will likely end without intervention, as SCP-816 requires access to SCP-816-1 in order to survive, and is not capable of moving SCP-816-1

Under Description - without SCP-816-1, SCP-816 would likely adapt to gain energy in a way that would allow it to expand beyond Site-P/██

One should be changed. Since they are dependent on it, I would suggest that the Containment be changed to have Agents periodically winding the Grandfather Clock to remove the possibility of a breach.







